help.descr:

    Penalty objects represent a weighted p-norm of an arbitrary
    signal, i.e. P(z) = \| Q z \|_p.


    Four types of norms are supported:


p=0 corresponds to penalization direct penalization
      of the quantity Qz, i.e., P(z) = Q z;

p=1 is the standard vector 1-norm;

p=Inf is the standard vector /infty-norm;

p=2 represents the squared 2-norm, i.e.,
      P(z) = z^T Q z.


    Instances of the Penalty class expose two properties for
    read/write access:


Q: the weighting matrix;

norm: the norm type (see above)
